<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>Is marriage registration compulsory?</h3>
<p>
Yes, marriage registration is legally required and a marriage certificate is mandatory for many official purposes.
</p>

<h3>Which law applies to marriage registration?</h3>
<p>
Marriage can be registered under the Hindu Marriage Act or Special Marriage Act depending on the case.
</p>

<h3>Why should I consult a marriage registration lawyer?</h3>
<p>
A lawyer ensures correct documentation, legal compliance and avoids delays or rejection of your application.
</p>

